  "enhanced_information": "Renin is produced by juxtaglomerular cells in the kidneys, confirming it is part of the renal system. Angiotensin I is not produced directly by the renal system; it is formed in the bloodstream from angiotensinogen by the action of renin, which is produced in the kidneys. Erythropoietin is produced by interstitial fibroblasts in the kidneys, making it part of the renal system. 1,25-Dihydroxyvitamin D (1,25DHCC) is the active form of vitamin D, which is converted in the kidneys, thus it is also produced by the renal system. Therefore, the only peptide not produced by the renal system is Angiotensin I."
